    "created_at": "2012-02-09T02:56:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-02-09T02:56:57Z",
    "body": "I am not sure... I rather think that parents with outstanding supervised children should not be considered dead until those children are dead (in particular, they should not send out their join message, because even if they succeed, they may yet fail due to failure propagation).  Of course this doesn't mean that the parent's resources shouldn't be collected, but the child will probably need sort of ref.  \n",
